         <abstract>
            <p>We discuss the use of Newton's method for computing Gauss-Kronrod quadrature formulae from modified moments. The underlying nonlinear maps are analyzed from the point of view of numerical condition. A method is indicated of computing the polynomial whose zeros are the Kronrod nodes. Examples include Gauss-Kronrod formulae for integrals with a logarithmic and algebraic singularity at one endpoint. Pertinent numerical results are tabulated in the supplements section at the end of this issue.</p>
          </abstract>
